  </div>

  <!-- What's New -->
  <h2 id="whats-new">What's New in v2.2</h2>
  <p>
    v2.2 is a single-focus release: post-quantum hybrid signing. All other protocol semantics
    are identical to v2.1. The only breaking change is that v2.2 implementations MUST generate
    an ML-DSA-65 key at boot and attach <code>pq_sig</code> to all signed messages.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>ML-DSA-65 key generation at boot</strong> — <code>castor/rcan/message_signing.py</code> generates <code>pq_signing.key</code> alongside <code>signing_key.pem</code></li>
    <li><strong><code>pq_sig</code> envelope field</strong> (field 16) — ML-DSA-65 signature block added to all signed messages</li>
    <li><strong>Hybrid firmware attestation</strong> — <code>castor attest sign</code> adds ML-DSA-65 signature to firmware manifests</li>
    <li><strong>RRF JWT ML-DSA flag</strong> — M2M_TRUSTED tokens carry <code>pq_alg: "ml-dsa-65"</code> when issuer supports PQ</li>
    <li><strong>rcan-py 1.2.0</strong> — <code>MLDSAKeyPair</code>, hybrid <code>sign_message()</code>, <code>verify_message(pq_trusted_keys=...)</code></li>
    <li><strong>rcan-ts 1.2.0</strong> — <code>MLDSAKeyPair</code>, <code>addPQSignature()</code>, <code>verifyPQSignature()</code></li>
  </ul>

