  <!-- §7.2 Message Signing (PQ hybrid) -->
  <h2 id="section-7-2">§7.2 Message Signing — Hybrid Mode</h2>
  <p>
    RCAN v2.2 introduces a <strong>hybrid signing period</strong>. All signed messages SHOULD carry
    two independent signatures:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>signature</code> — Ed25519 (backward-compatible with v2.1 receivers)</li>
    <li><code>pq_sig</code> — ML-DSA-65 (NIST FIPS 204, quantum-resistant)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Wire Format</h3>
  <pre class="bg-surface-2 rounded p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code>{`{
  "rcan": "2.2.0",
  "cmd": "move_forward",
  "target": "rcan://rrf.rcan.dev/acme/arm/v2/unit-001",
  "params": { "distance_m": 1.0 },
  "timestamp": "2026-03-26T00:00:00Z",

  // Ed25519 — backward-compat with v2.1
  "signature": {
    "alg": "ed25519",
    "kid": "b08ef96b",
    "sig": "<base64url Ed25519 sig>"
  },

  // ML-DSA-65 — v2.2 PQ hybrid (FIPS 204)
  "pq_sig": {
    "alg": "ml-dsa-65",
    "kid": "817cd3ff",
    "sig": "<base64url ML-DSA-65 sig, ~4412 chars>"
  }
}`}</code></pre>

