  <!-- §7.4 PQ Transition Timeline -->
  <h2 id="section-7-4">§7.4 Post-Quantum Transition Timeline</h2>
  <p>
    Google revised Q-Day (a cryptographically-relevant quantum computer capable of breaking RSA/ECC)
    to <strong>2029</strong> (March 2026). NIST finalized three PQ standards in August 2024:
    <a href="https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/FIPS/NIST.FIPS.204.pdf">FIPS 204 (ML-DSA)</a>,
    <a href="https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/fips/nist.fips.205.pdf">FIPS 205 (SLH-DSA)</a>,
    and <a href="https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/fips/nist.fips.203.pdf">FIPS 203 (ML-KEM)</a>.
    NIST IR 8547 mandates removal of quantum-vulnerable algorithms from U.S. government systems by 2035;
    practical deadline for robot firmware attestation signatures is 2029 (store-now-decrypt-later risk).
  </p>

  <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse mt-4 mb-8">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-surface-2">
        <th class="text-left p-2 border border-border">Period</th>
        <th class="text-left p-2 border border-border">Phase</th>
        <th class="text-left p-2 border border-border">Requirements</th>
