    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Why ML-DSA-65 (not SLH-DSA)?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ML-DSA-65</strong> (CRYSTALS-Dilithium, NIST security level 3): lattice-based, fast (~1ms sign/verify), 1952-byte public key. Primary choice for all RCAN signing.</li>
    <li><strong>SLH-DSA</strong> (SPHINCS+): hash-based, no lattice assumptions, conservative backup for very long-lived keys (&gt;10yr). Larger signatures (~7–50KB). RCAN MAY support in v3.0.</li>
    <li><strong>ML-KEM</strong> (Kyber): key encapsulation only — no RCAN use case yet (no ECDH in the wire protocol).</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- SDK -->
  <h2 id="sdk">SDK Quick-Start</h2>

  <h3>Python (rcan-py 1.2.0)</h3>
  <pre class="bg-surface-2 rounded p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code>{`pip install "rcan[pq]"   # includes dilithium-py

from rcan.signing import KeyPair, MLDSAKeyPair, sign_message, verify_message
from rcan import RCANMessage, RobotURI

# Generate key pairs once (at boot)
ed_kp  = KeyPair.generate();   ed_kp.save_private("~/.rcan/operator.pem")
pq_kp  = MLDSAKeyPair.generate(); pq_kp.save("~/.rcan/operator_pq.key")

# Hybrid sign (v2.2)
msg    = RCANMessage(cmd="move_forward", target=uri, params={"distance_m": 1.0})
signed = sign_message(msg, ed_kp, pq_keypair=pq_kp)
# → signed.signature  = { alg: "ed25519",   kid: "...", value: "..." }
# → signed.pq_sig     = { alg: "ml-dsa-65", kid: "...", value: "..." }

# Hybrid verify
pub_ed = KeyPair.from_public_pem(ed_pub_pem)
pub_pq = MLDSAKeyPair.from_public_bytes(pq_pub_bytes)
verify_message(signed, [pub_ed], pq_trusted_keys=[pub_pq])   # raises on failure
verify_message(signed, [pub_ed], require_pq=True)             # enforce PQ presence`}</code></pre>

  <h3>TypeScript (rcan-ts 1.2.0)</h3>
  <pre class="bg-surface-2 rounded p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code>{`npm install rcan @noble/post-quantum

import { RCANMessage } from "rcan";
import { MLDSAKeyPair, addPQSignature, verifyPQSignature } from "rcan";

// Generate key pair once
const pqKp = await MLDSAKeyPair.generate();

// Sign (call existing Ed25519 path first, then add ML-DSA)
const msg    = new RCANMessage({ cmd: "move_forward", target: uri, params: {} });
const signed = await addPQSignature(msg, pqKp);
// signed.pqSig = { alg: "ml-dsa-65", kid: "...", sig: "..." }

// Verify
const pubPq = await MLDSAKeyPair.fromPublicKey(pqPubBytes);
await verifyPQSignature(signed, [pubPq]);           // throws on failure
await verifyPQSignature(signed, [pubPq], true);     // requirePQ = true`}</code></pre>

